<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
TauDEM is a suite of Digital Elevation Model (DEM) tools for the extraction and analysis of hydrologic information from topography as represented by a DEM.
</para>
<!-- <formalpara><title>aread8</title> -->
<refsect2><title>aread8</title>
<para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><replaceable>basefilename</replaceable> is the name of the raw digital elevation model</listitem>
<listitem><replaceable>pfile</replaceable> is the D8 flow direction input file.</listitem>
<listitem><replaceable>afile</replaceable> is the D8 area output file.</listitem>
<listitem><replaceable>shfile</replaceable> is the optional outlet shape input file.</listitem>
<listitem><replaceable>wfile</replaceable> is the optional weight grid input file.</listitem>
<listitem><option>-nc</option> overrides edge contamination checking</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
The following are appended to the file names
before the files are opened:
ad8   D8 contributing area file (output)
</para>
</refsect2>
